'\x3cdiv id \x3d "section_14"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d "Iteration_methods"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch4 class \x3d "editable"\x3e\x3cspan\x3eIteration methods\x3c/span\x3e\x3c/h4\x3e\n\x3cp\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eSeveral methods take as arguments functions to be called back while processing the array. When these methods are called, the \x3ccode\x3elength\x3c/code\x3e of the array is sampled, and any element added beyond this length from within the callback is not visited. Other changes to the array (setting the value of or deleting an element) may affect the results of the operation if the method visits the changed element afterwards. While the specific behavior of these methods in such cases is well-defined, you should not rely upon it so as not to confuse others who might read your code. If you must mutate the array, copy into a new array instead.\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3cdl\x3e \x3cdt\x3e\x3ca title \x3d "en/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/filter" rel \x3d "internal" href \x3d "https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/filter"\x3efilter\x3c/a\x3e \n\x3cspan style \x3d "border: 1px solid rgb(129, 129, 81); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 225); font-size: x-small; white-space: nowrap; padding: 2px;"\x3eRequires \x3ca rel \x3d "custom" href \x3d "https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/New_in_JavaScript/1.6"\x3eJavaScript 1.6\x3c/a\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\n\x3c/dt\x3e \x3cdd\x3eCreates a new array with all of the elements of this array for which the provided filtering function returns true.\x3c/dd\x3e \x3cdt\x3e\x3ca title \x3d "en/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/forEach" rel \x3d "internal" href \x3d "https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/forEach"\x3eforEach\x3c/a\x3e \n\x3cspan style \x3d "border: 1px solid rgb(129, 129, 81); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 225); font-size: x-small; white-space: nowrap; padding: 2px;"\x3eRequires \x3ca rel \x3d "custom" href \x3d "https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/New_in_JavaScript/1.6"\x3eJavaScript 1.6\x3c/a\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\n\x3c/dt\x3e \x3cdd\x3eCalls a function for each element in the array.\x3c/dd\x3e \x3cdt\x3e\x3ca title \x3d "en/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/every" rel \x3d "internal" href \x3d "https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/every"\x3eevery\x3c/a\x3e \n\x3cspan style \x3d "border: 1px solid rgb(129, 129, 81); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 225); font-size: x-small; white-space: nowrap; padding: 2px;"\x3eRequires \x3ca rel \x3d "custom" href \x3d "https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/New_in_JavaScript/1.6"\x3eJavaScript 1.6\x3c/a\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\n\x3c/dt\x3e \x3cdd\x3eReturns true if every element in this array satisfies the provided testing function.\x3c/dd\x3e \x3cdt\x3e\x3ca title \x3d "en/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/map" rel \x3d "internal" href \x3d "https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/map"\x3emap\x3c/a\x3e \n\x3cspan style \x3d "border: 1px solid rgb(129, 129, 81); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 225); font-size: x-small; white-space: nowrap; padding: 2px;"\x3eRequires \x3ca rel \x3d "custom" href \x3d "https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/New_in_JavaScript/1.6"\x3eJavaScript 1.6\x3c/a\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\n\x3c/dt\x3e \x3cdd\x3eCreates a new array with the results of calling a provided function on every element in this array.\x3c/dd\x3e \x3cdt\x3e\x3ca title \x3d "en/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/some" rel \x3d "internal" href \x3d "https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/some"\x3esome\x3c/a\x3e \n\x3cspan style \x3d "border: 1px solid rgb(129, 129, 81); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 225); font-size: x-small; white-space: nowrap; padding: 2px;"\x3eRequires \x3ca rel \x3d "custom" href \x3d "https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/New_in_JavaScript/1.6"\x3eJavaScript 1.6\x3c/a\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\n\x3c/dt\x3e \x3cdd\x3eReturns true if at least one element in this array satisfies the provided testing function.\x3c/dd\x3e \x3cdt\x3e\x3ca title \x3d "en/JavaScript/Reference/Objects/Array/reduce" rel \x3d "internal" href \x3d "https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/Reduce"\x3ereduce\x3c/a\x3e \n\x3cspan style \x3d "border: 1px solid rgb(129, 129, 81); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 225); font-size: x-small; white-space: nowrap; padding: 2px;"\x3eRequires \x3ca rel \x3d "custom" href \x3d "https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/New_in_JavaScript/1.8"\x3eJavaScript 1.8\x3c/a\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\n\x3c/dt\x3e \x3cdd\x3eApply a function simultaneously against two values of the array (from left-to-right) as to reduce it to a single value.\x3c/dd\x3e \x3cdt\x3e\x3ca title \x3d "en/JavaScript/Reference/Objects/Array/reduceRight" rel \x3d "internal" href \x3d "https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/ReduceRight"\x3ereduceRight\x3c/a\x3e \n\x3cspan style \x3d "border: 1px solid rgb(129, 129, 81); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 225); font-size: x-small; white-space: nowrap; padding: 2px;"\x3eRequires \x3ca rel \x3d "custom" href \x3d "https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/New_in_JavaScript/1.8"\x3eJavaScript 1.8\x3c/a\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\n\x3c/dt\x3e \x3cdd\x3eApply a function simultaneously against two values of the array (from right-to-left) as to reduce it to a single value.\x3c/dd\x3e\n\x3c/dl\x3e\n\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3c/div\x3e',
"\x3cdiv id \x3d \"section_15\"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d \"Examples\"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch2 class \x3d \"editable\"\x3eExamples\x3c/h2\x3e\n\x3cdiv id \x3d \"section_16\"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d \"Example:_Creating_an_Array\"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch3 class \x3d \"editable\"\x3eExample: Creating an Array\x3c/h3\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eThe following example creates an array, \x3ccode\x3emsgArray\x3c/code\x3e, with a length of 0, then assigns values to \x3ccode\x3emsgArray[0]\x3c/code\x3e and \x3ccode\x3emsgArray[99]\x3c/code\x3e, changing the length of the array to 100.\x3c/p\x3e\n\r\n          \x3cpre name \x3d \"code\" class \x3d \"js\"\x3evar msgArray \x3d new Array();\nmsgArray[0] \x3d \x26quot;Hello\x26quot;;\nmsgArray[99] \x3d \x26quot;world\x26quot;;\n\nif (msgArray.length \x3d\x3d 100)\n   print(\x26quot;The length is 100.\x26quot;);\x3c/pre\x3e\r\n        \n\x3c/div\x3e\x3cdiv id \x3d \"section_17\"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d \"Example:_Creating_a_Two-dimensional_Array\"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch3 class \x3d \"editable\"\x3eExample: Creating a Two-dimensional Array\x3c/h3\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eThe following creates chess board as a two dimensional array of strings. The first move is made by copying the 'P' in 6,4 to 4,4. The position 4,4 is left blank.\x3c/p\x3e\n\r\n          \x3cpre name \x3d \"code\" class \x3d \"js\"\x3evar board \x3d \n[ ['R','N','B','Q','K','B','N','R'],\n  ['P','P','P','P','P','P','P','P'],\n  [' ',' ',' ',' ',' ',' ',' ',' '],\n  [' ',' ',' ',' ',' ',' ',' ',' '],\n  [' ',' ',' ',' ',' ',' ',' ',' '],\n  [' ',' ',' ',' ',' ',' ',' ',' '],\n  ['p','p','p','p','p','p','p','p'],\n  ['r','n','b','q','k','b','n','r']];\nprint(board.join('\\n') + '\\n\\n');\n\n// Move King's Pawn forward 2\nboard[4][4] \x3d board[6][4];\nboard[6][4] \x3d ' ';\nprint(board.join('\\n'));\x3c/pre\x3e\r\n        \n\x3cp\x3eHere is the output:\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3cpre class \x3d \"eval\"\x3eR,N,B,Q,K,B,N,R\nP,P,P,P,P,P,P,P\n , , , , , , , \n , , , , , , , \n , , , , , , , \n , , , , , , , \np,p,p,p,p,p,p,p\nr,n,b,q,k,b,n,r\n\nR,N,B,Q,K,B,N,R\nP,P,P,P,P,P,P,P\n , , , , , , , \n , , , , , , , \n , , , ,p, , , \n , , , , , , , \np,p,p,p, ,p,p,p\nr,n,b,q,k,b,n,r\n\x3c/pre\x3e\n\x3c/div\x3e\x3c/div\x3e",
