'\x3cdiv id \x3d "section_2"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d "Syntax"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch3 class \x3d "editable"\x3eSyntax\x3c/h3\x3e\n\x3cpre class \x3d "eval"\x3e\nif (\x3cem\x3econdition\x3c/em\x3e)\n   \x3cem\x3estatement1\x3c/em\x3e\n[else\n   \x3cem\x3estatement2\x3c/em\x3e]\n\x3c/pre\x3e\n\x3c/div\x3e','\x3cdiv id \x3d "section_3"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d "Parameters"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch3 class \x3d "editable"\x3eParameters\x3c/h3\x3e\n\x3cdl\x3e \x3cdt\x3e\x3ccode\x3econdition\x3c/code\x3e\x26nbsp;\x3c/dt\x3e \x3cdd\x3eAn expression that evaluates to true or false.\x3c/dd\x3e\n\x3c/dl\x3e\n\x3cdl\x3e \x3cdt\x3e\x3ccode\x3estatement1\x3c/code\x3e\x26nbsp;\x3c/dt\x3e \x3cdd\x3eStatement that is executed if \x3ccode\x3econdition\x3c/code\x3e evaluates to true. Can be any statement, including further nested \x3ccode\x3eif\x3c/code\x3e statements. To execute multiple statements, use a \x3ca title \x3d "en/JavaScript/Reference/Statements/block" rel \x3d "internal" href \x3d "https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/Reference/Statements/block"\x3eblock\x3c/a\x3e statement ({ ... }) to group those statements.\x3c/dd\x3e\n\x3c/dl\x3e\n\x3cdl\x3e \x3cdt\x3e\x3ccode\x3estatement2\x3c/code\x3e\x26nbsp;\x3c/dt\x3e \x3cdd\x3eStatement that is executed if \x3ccode\x3econdition\x3c/code\x3e evaluates to false and the \x3ccode\x3eelse\x3c/code\x3e clause exists. Can be any statement, including block statements and further nested \x3ccode\x3eif\x3c/code\x3e statements.\x3c/dd\x3e\n\x3c/dl\x3e\n\x3c/div\x3e',
'\x3cdiv id \x3d "section_4"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d "Description"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch3 class \x3d "editable"\x3eDescription\x3c/h3\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eMultiple \x3ccode\x3eif...else\x3c/code\x3e statements can be nested to create an \x3ccode\x3eelse if\x3c/code\x3e clause:\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3cpre class \x3d "eval"\x3e\nif (\x3cem\x3econdition1\x3c/em\x3e)\n   \x3cem\x3estatement1\x3c/em\x3e\nelse if (\x3cem\x3econdition2\x3c/em\x3e)\n   \x3cem\x3estatement2\x3c/em\x3e\nelse if (\x3cem\x3econdition3\x3c/em\x3e)\n   \x3cem\x3estatement3\x3c/em\x3e\n...\nelse\n   \x3cem\x3estatementN\x3c/em\x3e\n\x3c/pre\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eTo see how this works, this is how it would look like if the nesting were properly indented:\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3cpre class \x3d "eval"\x3e\nif (\x3cem\x3econdition1\x3c/em\x3e)\n   \x3cem\x3estatement1\x3c/em\x3e\nelse\n   if (\x3cem\x3econdition2\x3c/em\x3e)\n      \x3cem\x3estatement2\x3c/em\x3e\n   else\n      if (\x3cem\x3econdition3\x3c/em\x3e)\n...\n\x3c/pre\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eTo execute multiple statements within a clause, use a block statement (\x3ccode\x3e{ ... }\x3c/code\x3e) to group those statements. In general, it is a good practice to always use block statements, especially in code involving nested \x3ccode\x3eif\x3c/code\x3e statements:\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3cpre class \x3d "eval"\x3e\nif (\x3cem\x3econdition\x3c/em\x3e) {\n   \x3cem\x3estatements1\x3c/em\x3e\n} else {\n   \x3cem\x3estatements2\x3c/em\x3e\n}\n\x3c/pre\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eDo not confuse the primitive boolean values \x3ccode\x3etrue\x3c/code\x3e and \x3ccode\x3efalse\x3c/code\x3e with the true and false values of the \x3ca title \x3d "en/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Boolean" rel \x3d "internal" href \x3d "https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Boolean"\x3eBoolean\x3c/a\x3e object. Any value that is not \x3ccode\x3eundefined\x3c/code\x3e, \x3ccode\x3enull\x3c/code\x3e, \x3ccode\x3e0\x3c/code\x3e, \x3ccode\x3eNaN\x3c/code\x3e, or the empty string (\x3ccode\x3e\x26quot;\x26quot;\x3c/code\x3e), and any object, including a Boolean object whose value is false, evaluates to true when passed to a conditional statement. For example:\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3cpre class \x3d "eval"\x3e\nvar b \x3d new Boolean(false);\nif (b) // this condition evaluates to true\n\x3c/pre\x3e\n\x3c/div\x3e',
