'\x3cdiv id \x3d "section_2"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d "Syntax"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch3 class \x3d "editable"\x3e Syntax \x3c/h3\x3e\n\x3cp\x3e\x3ccode\x3e\nimport \x3ci\x3eobjectName\x3c/i\x3e.\x3ci\x3ename1\x3c/i\x3e, \x3ci\x3eobjectName\x3c/i\x3e.\x3ci\x3ename2\x3c/i\x3e, ..., \x3ci\x3eobjectName\x3c/i\x3e.\x3ci\x3enameN\x3c/i\x3e;\n\x3c/code\x3e\n\x3c/p\x3e\x3cp\x3e\x3ccode\x3e\nimport \x3ci\x3eobjectName\x3c/i\x3e.\x3ci\x3e*\x3c/i\x3e;\n\x3c/code\x3e\n\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3c/div\x3e','\x3cdiv id \x3d "section_3"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d "Parameters"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch3 class \x3d "editable"\x3e Parameters \x3c/h3\x3e\n\x3cdl\x3e\x3cdt\x3e \x3ccode\x3eobjectName\x3c/code\x3e\x26nbsp;\x3c/dt\x3e\x3cdd\x3e Name of the object that will receive the imported names.\n\x3c/dd\x3e\x3c/dl\x3e\n\x3cdl\x3e\x3cdt\x3e \x3ccode\x3enameN\x3c/code\x3e\x26nbsp;\x3c/dt\x3e\x3cdd\x3e Property, function, or object to be imported.\n\x3c/dd\x3e\x3c/dl\x3e\n\x3c/div\x3e',
'\x3cdiv id \x3d "section_4"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d "Description"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch3 class \x3d "editable"\x3e Description \x3c/h3\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eThe \x3ccode\x3eobjectName\x3c/code\x3e parameter is the name of the object that will receive the imported names. For example, if \x3ccode\x3ef\x3c/code\x3e and \x3ccode\x3ep\x3c/code\x3e have been exported, and if \x3ccode\x3eobj\x3c/code\x3e is an object from the importing script, the following code makes \x3ccode\x3ef\x3c/code\x3e and \x3ccode\x3ep\x3c/code\x3e accessible in the importing script as properties of \x3ccode\x3eobj\x3c/code\x3e.\n\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3cpre class \x3d "eval"\x3eimport obj.f, obj.p;\n\x3c/pre\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eThe first syntax imports the specified properties, functions, and objects from the exported script.\n\x3c/p\x3e\x3cp\x3eThe second syntax imports all properties, functions, and objects from the exported script.\n\x3c/p\x3e\x3cp\x3eTypically, information in a signed script is available only to scripts signed by the same principals. By exporting (using the \x3ccode\x3e\x3ca rel \x3d "internal" href \x3d "https://developer.mozilla.org/en/Core_JavaScript_1.5_Reference/Statements/export" title \x3d "en/Core_JavaScript_1.5_Reference/Statements/export"\x3eexport\x3c/a\x3e\x3c/code\x3e statement) properties, functions, or objects, a signed script makes this information available to any script (signed or unsigned). The receiving script uses the \x3ccode\x3eimport\x3c/code\x3e statement to access the information.\n\x3c/p\x3e\x3cp\x3eThe script must load the export script into a window, frame, or layer before it can import and use any exported properties, functions, and objects.\n\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3c/div\x3e',
