'\x3cdiv id \x3d "section_4"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d "Avoid_using_labels"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch2 class \x3d "editable"\x3eAvoid using labels\x3c/h2\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eLabels are not very commonly used in JavaScript since they make programs harder to read an understand. As much as possible, avoid using labels and, depending on the cases, prefer \x3ca title \x3d "function" rel \x3d "internal" href \x3d "https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/Reference/Statements/function"\x3ecalling functions\x3c/a\x3e or \x3ca title \x3d "throw" rel \x3d "internal" href \x3d "https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/Reference/Statements/throw"\x3ethrowing\x3c/a\x3e an error.\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3c/div\x3e',
