'\x3cdiv id \x3d "section_2"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d "Syntax"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch2 class \x3d "editable"\x3eSyntax\x3c/h2\x3e\n\x3cpre class \x3d "eval"\x3e\nswitch (\x3cem\x3eexpression\x3c/em\x3e) {\n   case \x3cem\x3elabel1\x3c/em\x3e:\n      \x3cem\x3estatements1\x3c/em\x3e\n      [break;]\n   case \x3cem\x3elabel2\x3c/em\x3e:\n      \x3cem\x3estatements2\x3c/em\x3e\n      [break;]\n   ...\n   case \x3cem\x3elabelN\x3c/em\x3e:\n      \x3cem\x3estatementsN\x3c/em\x3e\n      [break;]\n   default:\n      \x3cem\x3estatements_def\x3c/em\x3e\n      [break;]\n}\n\x3c/pre\x3e\n\x3c/div\x3e',
'\x3cdiv id \x3d "section_3"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d "Parameters"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch2 class \x3d "editable"\x3eParameters\x3c/h2\x3e\n\x3cdl\x3e \x3cdt\x3e\x3ccode\x3eexpression\x3c/code\x3e\x26nbsp;\x3c/dt\x3e \x3cdd\x3eAn expression matched against each label.\x3c/dd\x3e\n\x3c/dl\x3e\n\x3cdl\x3e \x3cdt\x3e\x3ccode\x3elabelN\x3c/code\x3e\x26nbsp;\x3c/dt\x3e \x3cdd\x3eIdentifier used to match against \x3ccode\x3eexpression\x3c/code\x3e.\x3c/dd\x3e\n\x3c/dl\x3e\n\x3cdl\x3e \x3cdt\x3e\x3ccode\x3estatementsN\x3c/code\x3e\x26nbsp;\x3c/dt\x3e \x3cdd\x3eStatements that are executed if \x3ccode\x3eexpression\x3c/code\x3e matches the associated label.\x3c/dd\x3e\n\x3c/dl\x3e\n\x3cdl\x3e \x3cdt\x3e\x3ccode\x3estatements_def\x3c/code\x3e\x26nbsp;\x3c/dt\x3e \x3cdd\x3eStatements that are executed if \x3ccode\x3eexpression\x3c/code\x3e does not match any label.\x3c/dd\x3e\n\x3c/dl\x3e\n\x3c/div\x3e',
'\x3cdiv id \x3d "section_4"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d "Description"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch2 class \x3d "editable"\x3eDescription\x3c/h2\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eIf a match is found, the program executes the associated statements. If multiple cases match the provided value, the first case that matches is selected, even if the cases are not equal to each other.\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eThe program first looks for a \x3ccode\x3ecase\x3c/code\x3e clause with a label matching the value of expression and then transfers control to that clause, executing the associated statements. If no matching label is found, the program looks for the optional \x3ccode\x3edefault\x3c/code\x3e clause, and if found, transfers control to that clause, executing the associated statements. If no \x3ccode\x3edefault\x3c/code\x3e clause is found, the program continues execution at the statement following the end of \x3ccode\x3eswitch\x3c/code\x3e. By convention, the \x3ccode\x3edefault\x3c/code\x3e clause is the last clause, but it does not need to be so.\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eThe optional \x3ccode\x3e\x3ca title \x3d "en/Core_JavaScript_1.5_Reference/Statements/break" rel \x3d "internal" href \x3d "https://developer.mozilla.org/en/Core_JavaScript_1.5_Reference/Statements/break"\x3ebreak\x3c/a\x3e\x3c/code\x3e statement associated with each case label ensures that the program breaks out of switch once the matched statement is executed and continues execution at the statement following switch. If \x3ccode\x3ebreak\x3c/code\x3e is omitted, the program continues execution at the next statement in the \x3ccode\x3eswitch\x3c/code\x3e statement.\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3c/div\x3e',
'\x3cdiv id \x3d "section_5"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d "Examples"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch2 class \x3d "editable"\x3eExamples\x3c/h2\x3e\n\x3cdiv id \x3d "section_6"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d "Example:_Using_switch"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch3 class \x3d "editable"\x3eExample: Using \x3ccode\x3eswitch\x3c/code\x3e\x3c/h3\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eIn the following example, if \x3ccode\x3eexpression\x3c/code\x3e evaluates to \x26quot;Bananas\x26quot;, the program matches the value with case \x26quot;Bananas\x26quot; and executes the associated statement. When \x3ccode\x3ebreak\x3c/code\x3e is encountered, the program breaks out of \x3ccode\x3eswitch\x3c/code\x3e and executes the statement following \x3ccode\x3eswitch\x3c/code\x3e. If \x3ccode\x3ebreak\x3c/code\x3e were omitted, the statement for case \x26quot;Cherries\x26quot; would also be executed.\x3c/p\x3e\n\r\n          \x3cpre name \x3d "code" class \x3d "js"\x3eswitch (expr) {\n   case \x26quot;Oranges\x26quot;:\n      document.write(\x26quot;Oranges are $0.59 a pound.\x26lt;br\x26gt;\x26quot;);\n      break;\n   case \x26quot;Apples\x26quot;:\n      document.write(\x26quot;Apples are $0.32 a pound.\x26lt;br\x26gt;\x26quot;);\n      break;\n   case \x26quot;Bananas\x26quot;:\n      document.write(\x26quot;Bananas are $0.48 a pound.\x26lt;br\x26gt;\x26quot;);\n      break;\n   case \x26quot;Cherries\x26quot;:\n      document.write(\x26quot;Cherries are $3.00 a pound.\x26lt;br\x26gt;\x26quot;);\n      break;\n   case \x26quot;Mangoes\x26quot;:\n   case \x26quot;Papayas\x26quot;:\n      document.write(\x26quot;Mangoes and papayas are $2.79 a pound.\x26lt;br\x26gt;\x26quot;);\n      break;\n   default:\n      document.write(\x26quot;Sorry, we are out of \x26quot; + expr + \x26quot;.\x26lt;br\x26gt;\x26quot;);\n}\ndocument.write(\x26quot;Is there anything else you\'d like?\x26lt;br\x26gt;\x26quot;);\x3c/pre\x3e\r\n        \n\x3cp\x3e\x26nbsp;\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3cp\x3e\x3c/p\x3e\x3c/div\x3e\x3c/div\x3e',
