'\x3cdiv id \x3d "section_4"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d "Description"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch2 class \x3d "editable"\x3eDescription\x3c/h2\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eIn JavaScript, a setter can be used to execute a function whenever a specified property is attempted to be changed. Setters are most often used in conjunction with getters to create a type of pseudo-property. It is not possible to simultaneously have a setter on a property that holds an actual value.\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3cp\x3e\n\x3cdiv style \x3d "border: 0px none ; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 10px; background-color: rgb(254, 244, 156); text-align: center;"\x3e\x3cp style \x3d "margin: 4px 0px; font-weight: bold;"\x3e\x3ca rel \x3d "custom" href \x3d "https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/New_in_JavaScript/1.8.1"\x3eJavaScript 1.8.1\x3c/a\x3e note\x3c/p\x3e\x3cp style \x3d "margin: 4px 0px;"\x3eStarting in JavaScript 1.8.1, setters are no longer called when setting properties in object and array initializers.\x3c/p\x3e\x3c/div\x3e\x3c/p\x3e\n\n\x3cdiv style \x3d "border: 0px none ; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px 10px; background-color: rgb(254, 244, 156); text-align: center;"\x3e\x3cp style \x3d "margin: 4px 0px; font-weight: bold;"\x3e\x3ca rel \x3d "custom" href \x3d "https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/New_in_JavaScript/1.8.5"\x3eJavaScript 1.8.5\x3c/a\x3e note\x3c/p\x3e\x3cp style \x3d "margin: 4px 0px;"\x3e\x3cp style \x3d "text-align: left;"\x3eStarting in JavaScript 1.8.5, \x3ccode\x3eset\x3c/code\x3e operator:\x3c/p\x3e\n  \x3cul style \x3d "text-align: left;"\x3e\n    \x3cli\x3ecan have an identifier which is either a number or a string;\x3c/li\x3e\n    \x3cli\x3emust have exactly one parameter (see \n      \x3ca href \x3d "http://whereswalden.com/2010/08/22/incompatible-es5-change-literal-getter-and-setter-functions-must-now-have-exactly-zero-or-one-arguments/" class \x3d "external" rel \x3d "external nofollow" target \x3d "_blank"\x3eIncompatible \x3cabbr title \x3d "ECMAScript 5th edition"\x3eES5\x3c/abbr\x3e change: literal getter and setter functions must now have exactly zero or one arguments\x3c/a\x3e\n      for more information);\x3c/li\x3e\n    \x3cli\x3emust not appear in an object literal with another \x3ccode\x3eset\x3c/code\x3e\n      or with a data entry for the same property (\x3ccode\x3e{ set x(v) { }, set x(v) { } }\x3c/code\x3e\n      and \x3ccode\x3e{ x: ..., set x(v) { } }\x3c/code\x3e are forbidden).\x3c/li\x3e\n  \x3c/ul\x3e\x3c/p\x3e\x3c/div\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eA setter can be removed using the \x3ca title \x3d "en/JavaScript/Reference/Operators/Special/delete" rel \x3d "internal" href \x3d "https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/Reference/Operators/Special/delete"\x3e\x3ccode\x3edelete\x3c/code\x3e\x3c/a\x3e operator.\x3c/p\x3e\x3c/div\x3e',
'\x3cdiv id \x3d "section_5"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d "Examples"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch2 class \x3d "editable"\x3eExamples\x3c/h2\x3e\n\x3cdiv id \x3d "section_6"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d "Example:_Defining_a_setter_with_the_set_operator"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d "Defining_a_setter_with_the_set_operator"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch3 class \x3d "editable"\x3eDefining a setter with the \x3ccode\x3eset\x3c/code\x3e operator\x3c/h3\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eThis will define a pseudo-property \x3ccode\x3ecurrent\x3c/code\x3e of object \x3ccode\x3eo\x3c/code\x3e that, when assigned a value, will update \x3ccode\x3elog\x3c/code\x3e with that value:\x3c/p\x3e\n\r\n          \x3cpre name \x3d "code" class \x3d "js"\x3evar o \x3d {\n  set current (str) {\n    return this.log[this.log.length] \x3d str;\n  },\n  log: []\n}\x3c/pre\x3e\r\n        \n\x3cp\x3eNote that \x3ccode\x3ecurrent\x3c/code\x3e is not defined and any attempts to access it will result in \x3ccode\x3eundefined\x3c/code\x3e\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3c/div\x3e\x3cdiv id \x3d "section_7"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d "Example:_Removing_a_setter_with_the_delete_operator"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d "Removing_a_setter_with_the_delete_operator"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch3 class \x3d "editable"\x3eRemoving a setter with the \x3ccode\x3edelete\x3c/code\x3e operator\x3c/h3\x3e\n\r\n          \x3cpre name \x3d "code" class \x3d "js"\x3edelete o.current;\x3c/pre\x3e\r\n        \n\x3c/div\x3e\x3c/div\x3e',
