"\x3cdiv id \x3d \"section_5\"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d \"Examples\"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch2 class \x3d \"editable\"\x3eExamples\x3c/h2\x3e\n\x3cdiv id \x3d \"section_6\"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d \"Normal_cases\"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch3 class \x3d \"editable\"\x3eNormal cases\x3c/h3\x3e\n\r\n          \x3cpre name \x3d \"code\" class \x3d \"js\"\x3e// Numbers\ntypeof 37 \x3d\x3d\x3d 'number';\ntypeof 3.14 \x3d\x3d\x3d 'number';\ntypeof Math.LN2 \x3d\x3d\x3d 'number';\ntypeof Infinity \x3d\x3d\x3d 'number';\ntypeof NaN \x3d\x3d\x3d 'number'; // Despite being \x26quot;Not-A-Number\x26quot;\ntypeof Number(1) \x3d\x3d\x3d 'number'; // but never use this form!\n\n// Strings\ntypeof \x26quot;\x26quot; \x3d\x3d\x3d 'string';\ntypeof \x26quot;bla\x26quot; \x3d\x3d\x3d 'string';\ntypeof (typeof 1) \x3d\x3d\x3d 'string'; // typeof always return a string\ntypeof String(\x26quot;abc\x26quot;) \x3d\x3d\x3d 'string'; // but never use this form!\n\n// Booleans\ntypeof true \x3d\x3d\x3d 'boolean';\ntypeof false \x3d\x3d\x3d 'boolean';\ntypeof Boolean(true) \x3d\x3d\x3d 'boolean'; // but never use this form!\n\n// Undefined\ntypeof undefined \x3d\x3d\x3d 'undefined';\ntypeof blabla \x3d\x3d\x3d 'undefined'; // an undefined variable\n\n// Objects\ntypeof {a:1} \x3d\x3d\x3d 'object';\ntypeof [1, 2, 4] \x3d\x3d\x3d 'object'; // use Array.isArray or Object.prototype.toString.call to differentiate regular objects from arrays\ntypeof new Date() \x3d\x3d\x3d 'object';\n\ntypeof new Boolean(true) \x3d\x3d\x3d 'object' // this is confusing. Don't use!\ntypeof new Number(1) \x3d\x3d\x3d 'object' // this is confusing. Don't use!\ntypeof new String(\x26quot;abc\x26quot;) \x3d\x3d\x3d 'object';  // this is confusing. Don't use!\n\n// Functions\ntypeof function(){} \x3d\x3d\x3d 'function';\ntypeof Math.sin \x3d\x3d\x3d 'function';\x3c/pre\x3e\r\n        \n\x3c/div\x3e\x3cdiv id \x3d \"section_7\"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d \"null\"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch3 class \x3d \"editable\"\x3e\x3ccode\x3enull\x3c/code\x3e\x3c/h3\x3e\n\r\n          \x3cpre name \x3d \"code\" class \x3d \"js\"\x3etypeof null \x3d\x3d\x3d 'object'; // This stands since the beginning of JavaScript\x3c/pre\x3e\r\n        \n\x3cp\x3eIn the first implementation of JavaScript, JavaScript values were represented as a type tag and a value. The type tag for objects was 0. \x3ccode\x3enull\x3c/code\x3e was represented as the NULL pointer (0x00 is most platforms). Consequently, null had 0 as type tag, hence the bogus \x3ccode\x3etypeof\x3c/code\x3e return value. (reference needed)\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eThis is planned on \x3ca class \x3d \" external\" rel \x3d \"external\" href \x3d \"http://wiki.ecmascript.org/doku.php?id\x3dharmony:typeof_null\" title \x3d \"http://wiki.ecmascript.org/doku.php?id\x3dharmony:typeof_null\" target \x3d \"_blank\"\x3ebeing fixed in the next version of ECMAScript\x3c/a\x3e (which will be available via an opt-in). It will result in \x3ccode\x3etypeof null \x3d\x3d\x3d 'null'\x3c/code\x3e.\x3c/p\x3e\x3c/div\x3e\x3cdiv id \x3d \"section_8\"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d \"Regular_expressions\"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch3 class \x3d \"editable\"\x3eRegular expressions\x3c/h3\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eCallable regular expressions were a non-standard addition in some browsers (need reference to say which).\x3c/p\x3e\n\r\n          \x3cpre name \x3d \"code\" class \x3d \"js\"\x3etypeof /s/ \x3d\x3d\x3d 'function'; // Chrome 1-12 ... // Non-conform to ECMAScript 5.1\ntypeof /s/ \x3d\x3d\x3d 'object'; // Firefox 5+ ...    // Conform to ECMAScript 5.1\x3c/pre\x3e\r\n         \x3c/div\x3e\x3cdiv id \x3d \"section_9\"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d \"Other_quirks\"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch3 class \x3d \"editable\"\x3eOther quirks\x3c/h3\x3e\n\x3cdiv id \x3d \"section_10\"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d \"alert_in_old_Internet_Explorer_versions\"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch4 class \x3d \"editable\"\x3e\x3ccode\x3ealert\x3c/code\x3e in old Internet Explorer versions\x3c/h4\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eOn IE 6, 7 and 8, \x3ccode\x3etypeof alert \x3d\x3d\x3d 'object'\x3c/code\x3e\x3c/p\x3e\x3c/div\x3e\x3c/div\x3e\x3c/div\x3e",
