'\x3cdiv id \x3d "section_2"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d "Description"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch2 class \x3d "editable"\x3eDescription\x3c/h2\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eThe name property returns the name of a function, or an empty string for anonymous functions:\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3cpre class \x3d "eval"\x3efunction doSomething() {}\nalert(doSomething.name); // alerts \x26quot;doSomething\x26quot;\n\x3c/pre\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eFunctions created with the syntax \x3ccode\x3enew \x3ca title \x3d "Function" rel \x3d "internal" href \x3d "https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function"\x3eFunction\x3c/a\x3e(...)\x3c/code\x3e or just \x3ccode\x3e\x3ca title \x3d "Function" rel \x3d "internal" href \x3d "https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function"\x3eFunction\x3c/a\x3e\x3c/code\x3e\x3ccode\x3e(...)\x3c/code\x3e have their name property set to \x26quot;anonymous\x26quot; on Firefox and Safari, or to an empty string on Chrome and Opera. This property is not supported on Internet Explorer.\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eNote that in these examples anonymous functions are created, so \x3ccode\x3ename\x3c/code\x3e returns an empty string:\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3cpre class \x3d "eval"\x3evar f \x3d function() { };\nvar object \x3d {\n  someMethod: function() {}\n};\n\nalert(f.name \x3d\x3d \x26quot;\x26quot;); // true\nalert(object.someMethod.name \x3d\x3d \x26quot;\x26quot;); // also true\n\x3c/pre\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eYou can define a function with a name in a \x3ca title \x3d "En/Core_JavaScript_1.5_Reference/Functions#Function_constructor_vs._function_declaration_vs._function_expression" rel \x3d "internal" href \x3d "https://developer.mozilla.org/En/Core_JavaScript_1.5_Reference/Functions#Function_constructor_vs._function_declaration_vs._function_expression"\x3efunction expression\x3c/a\x3e:\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3cpre class \x3d "eval"\x3evar object \x3d {\n  someMethod: function object_someMethod() {}\n};\nalert(object.someMethod.name); // alerts \x26quot;object_someMethod\x26quot;\n\ntry { object_someMethod } catch(e) { alert(e); }\n// ReferenceError: object_someMethod is not defined\n\x3c/pre\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eYou cannot change the \x3ccode\x3ename\x3c/code\x3e of a function, this property is read-only:\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3cpre class \x3d "eval"\x3evar object \x3d {\n  // anonymous\n  someMethod: function(){}\n};\nobject.someMethod.name \x3d \x26quot;someMethod\x26quot;;\nalert(object.someMethod.name); // empty string, someMethod is anonymous\n\x3c/pre\x3e\n\x3c/div\x3e',
