'\x3cdiv id \x3d "section_4"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d "Description"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch3 class \x3d "editable"\x3eDescription\x3c/h3\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eThe \x3ca title \x3d "en/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array" rel \x3d "internal" href \x3d "https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array"\x3eArray\x3c/a\x3e object overrides the \x3ccode\x3etoString\x3c/code\x3e method of \x3ca title \x3d "en/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object" rel \x3d "internal" href \x3d "https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object"\x3eObject\x3c/a\x3e. For Array objects, the \x3ccode\x3etoString\x3c/code\x3e method joins the array and returns one string containing each array element separated by commas. For example, the following code creates an array and uses \x3ccode\x3etoString\x3c/code\x3e to convert the array to a string.\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3cpre\x3evar monthNames \x3d [\'Jan\', \'Feb\', \'Mar\', \'Apr\'];\nvar myVar \x3d monthNames.toString(); // assigns \x26quot;Jan,Feb,Mar,Apr\x26quot; to myVar.\n\x3c/pre\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eJavaScript calls the \x3ccode\x3etoString\x3c/code\x3e method automatically when an array is to be represented as a text value or when an array is referred to in a string concatenation.\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3c/div\x3e',
