'\x3cdiv id \x3d "section_4"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d "Description"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch3 class \x3d "editable"\x3eDescription\x3c/h3\x3e\n\x3cp\x3e\x3ccode\x3efilter\x3c/code\x3e calls a provided \x3ccode\x3ecallback\x3c/code\x3e function once for each element in an array, and constructs a new array of all the values for which \x3ccode\x3ecallback\x3c/code\x3e returns a true value. \x3ccode\x3ecallback\x3c/code\x3e is invoked only for indexes of the array which have assigned values; it is not invoked for indexes which have been deleted or which have never been assigned values. Array elements which do not pass the \x3ccode\x3ecallback\x3c/code\x3e test are simply skipped, and are not included in the new array.\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3cp\x3e\x3ccode\x3ecallback\x3c/code\x3e is invoked with three arguments: the value of the element, the index of the element, and the Array object being traversed.\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eIf a \x3ccode\x3ethisObject\x3c/code\x3e parameter is provided to \x3ccode\x3efilter\x3c/code\x3e, it will be used as the \x3ccode\x3ethis\x3c/code\x3e for each invocation of the \x3ccode\x3ecallback\x3c/code\x3e. If it is not provided, or is \x3ccode\x3enull\x3c/code\x3e, the global object associated with \x3ccode\x3ecallback\x3c/code\x3e is used instead.\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3cp\x3e\x3ccode\x3efilter\x3c/code\x3e does not mutate the array on which it is called.\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eThe range of elements processed by \x3ccode\x3efilter\x3c/code\x3e is set before the first invocation of \x3ccode\x3ecallback\x3c/code\x3e. Elements which are appended to the array after the call to \x3ccode\x3efilter\x3c/code\x3e begins will not be visited by \x3ccode\x3ecallback\x3c/code\x3e. If existing elements of the array are changed, or deleted, their value as passed to \x3ccode\x3ecallback\x3c/code\x3e will be the value at the time \x3ccode\x3efilter\x3c/code\x3e visits them; elements that are deleted are not visited.\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3c/div\x3e',
