'\x3cdiv id \x3d "section_7"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d "Modifying_a_property"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch2 class \x3d "editable"\x3eModifying a property\x3c/h2\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eWhen the property already exists, \x3ccode\x3eObject.defineProperty\x3c/code\x3e attempts to modify the property according to the values in the descriptor and the object current configuration. If the old descriptor had its \x3cstrong\x3econfigurable\x3c/strong\x3e attribute set to \x3ccode\x3efalse\x3c/code\x3e (the property is said \x26quot;non-configurable\x26quot;), then no attribute besides \x3cstrong\x3ewritable\x3c/strong\x3e can be changed. In that case, it is also not possible to switch back and forth from data/accessor properties type (a property which would have been defined without \x3ccode\x3eget\x3c/code\x3e/\x3ccode\x3eset\x3c/code\x3e/\x3ccode\x3evalue\x3c/code\x3e/\x3ccode\x3ewritable\x3c/code\x3e is called \x26quot;generic\x26quot; and is \x26quot;typed\x26quot; as a data descriptor).\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eA \x3ca title \x3d "en/JavaScript/Reference/Global Objects/TypeError" rel \x3d "internal" href \x3d "https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/TypeError"\x3e\x3ccode\x3eTypeError\x3c/code\x3e\x3c/a\x3e is thrown when non-configurable property attributes are changed unless it\'s the \x3ccode\x3ewritable\x3c/code\x3e attribute or if the current and new values are equal.\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3c/div\x3e',
'\x3cdiv id \x3d "section_8"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d "Writable_attribute"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch2 class \x3d "editable"\x3eWritable attribute\x3c/h2\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eWhen the \x3ccode\x3ewritable\x3c/code\x3e property attribute is set to \x3ccode\x3efalse\x3c/code\x3e, the property is said to be \x26quot;non-writable\x26quot;. It cannot be assigned.\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3cdiv id \x3d "section_9"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d "Example_2"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch3 class \x3d "editable"\x3eExample\x3c/h3\x3e\n\r\n          \x3cpre name \x3d "code" class \x3d "js"\x3evar o \x3d {}; // Creates a new object\n\nObject.defineProperty(o, \x26quot;a\x26quot;, {value : 37,\n                               writable : false});\n\nalert(o.a); // alerts 37\no.a \x3d 25;\nalert(o.a); // alerts 37. The assignment didn\'t work. No error thrown\x3c/pre\x3e\r\n        \n\x3cp\x3eAs seen in the example, trying to write into the non-writable property doesn\'t change it but doesn\'t throw an error either.\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3c/div\x3e\x3c/div\x3e',
