'\x3cdiv id \x3d "section_12"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d "Configurable_attribute"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch2 class \x3d "editable"\x3eConfigurable attribute\x3c/h2\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eThe \x3ccode\x3econfigurable\x3c/code\x3e attribute controls at the same time whether the property can be deleted from the object and whether its attributes (other than \x3ccode\x3ewritable\x3c/code\x3e) can be changed.\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3cdiv id \x3d "section_13"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d "Example_4"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch3 class \x3d "editable"\x3eExample\x3c/h3\x3e\n\r\n          \x3cpre name \x3d "code" class \x3d "js"\x3evar o \x3d {};\nObject.defineProperty(o, \x26quot;a\x26quot;, { get : function(){return 1;}, \n                                configurable : false } );\n\nObject.defineProperty(o, \x26quot;a\x26quot;, {configurable : true}); // throws a TypeError\nObject.defineProperty(o, \x26quot;a\x26quot;, {enumerable : true}); // throws a TypeError\nObject.defineProperty(o, \x26quot;a\x26quot;, {set : function(){}}); // throws a TypeError (set was undefined previously)\nObject.defineProperty(o, \x26quot;a\x26quot;, {get : function(){return 1;}}); // throws a TypeError (even though the new get does exactly the same thing)\nObject.defineProperty(o, \x26quot;a\x26quot;, {value : 12}); // throws a TypeError\n\nalert(o.a); // alerts 1\ndelete o.a; // Nothing happens\nalert(o.a); // alerts 1\x3c/pre\x3e\r\n        \n\x3cp\x3eIf \x3ccode\x3eo.a\x3c/code\x3e \x3ccode\x3econfigurable\x3c/code\x3e attribute was \x3ccode\x3etrue\x3c/code\x3e, none of the error would be thrown and the property would be deleted at the end.\x3c/p\x3e\n\x3c/div\x3e\x3c/div\x3e',
