'\x3cdiv id \x3d "section_4"\x3e\x3cspan id \x3d "Description"\x3e\x3c/span\x3e\x3ch3 class \x3d "editable"\x3eDescription\x3c/h3\x3e\n\x3cp\x3eCharacters in a string are indexed from left to right. The index of the first character is 0, and the index of the last character of a string called \x3ccode\x3estringName\x3c/code\x3e is \x3ccode\x3estringName.length - 1\x3c/code\x3e.\x3c/p\x3e\n\r\n          \x3cpre name \x3d "code" class \x3d "js"\x3e\x26quot;Blue Whale\x26quot;.indexOf(\x26quot;Blue\x26quot;)    // returns 0\n\x26quot;Blue Whale\x26quot;.indexOf(\x26quot;Blute\x26quot;)   // returns -1\n\x26quot;Blue Whale\x26quot;.indexOf(\x26quot;Whale\x26quot;,0) // returns 5\n\x26quot;Blue Whale\x26quot;.indexOf(\x26quot;Whale\x26quot;,5) // returns 5\n\x26quot;Blue Whale\x26quot;.indexOf(\x26quot;\x26quot;,9)      // returns 9\n\x26quot;Blue Whale\x26quot;.indexOf(\x26quot;\x26quot;,10)     // returns 10\n\x26quot;Blue Whale\x26quot;.indexOf(\x26quot;\x26quot;,11)     // returns 10\x3c/pre\x3e\r\n        \n\x3cp\x3eThe \x3ccode\x3eindexOf\x3c/code\x3e method is case sensitive. For example, the following expression returns -1:\x3c/p\x3e\n\r\n          \x3cpre name \x3d "code" class \x3d "js"\x3e\x26quot;Blue Whale\x26quot;.indexOf(\x26quot;blue\x26quot;) // returns -1\x3c/pre\x3e\r\n        \n\x3cp\x3eNote that \'0\' doesn\'t evaluate to \x3ccode\x3etrue\x3c/code\x3e and \'-1\' doesn\'t evaluate to \x3ccode\x3efalse\x3c/code\x3e. Therefore, when checking if a specific string exists within another string the correct way to check would be:\x3c/p\x3e\n\r\n          \x3cpre name \x3d "code" class \x3d "js"\x3e\x26quot;Blue Whale\x26quot;.indexOf(\x26quot;Blue\x26quot;) !\x3d -1 // true\n\x26quot;Blue Whale\x26quot;.indexOf(\x26quot;Bloe\x26quot;) !\x3d -1 // false\x3c/pre\x3e\r\n        \n\x3c/div\x3e',
